# The font-subset stamp is compared BYTE-WISE by gui/build.rs — a CRLF checkout (Windows runner
# git ships autocrlf=true) must not rewrite it into "the pins changed", because the regen path
# needs unix-only dev tools. build.rs also normalizes CRLF on read; this stops the mangling at
# the source.
gui/assets/fonts/.subset-stamp -text
